# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

Successfully implemented Vercel Web Analytics for the TractotecPatron project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` version 1.6.1
- Updated package.json and package-lock.json with the new dependency

### 2. Analytics Integration
- Modified `src/App.jsx` to integrate Vercel Web Analytics
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/react";`
- Added `<Analytics />` component inside the Router, after the Layout component
- This placement ensures analytics tracks all routes properly with React Router

### 3. Implementation Details
- This is a React application built with Vite and React Router
- Following the Vercel documentation for React apps (create-react-app style implementation)
- The Analytics component is placed at the root level to track all page views and route changes
- The implementation includes automatic route detection for the following pages:
  - / (Home)
  - /servicios (Services)
  - /proyectos (Projects)
  - /nosotros (About)
  - /contacto (Contact)

### 4. Verification
- Build completed successfully with no errors related to the analytics implementation
- The analytics package is properly integrated and will start tracking once deployed to Vercel
- The implementation follows React best practices and maintains the existing code structure

## Next Steps for User

After deployment to Vercel:
1. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel Dashboard (Project → Analytics tab → Enable)
2. Deploy the application using `vercel deploy`
3. Visit `/_vercel/insights/view` endpoint to verify analytics is working
4. View analytics data in the Vercel Dashboard under the Analytics tab

## Notes
- The linter reported 2 pre-existing errors in other files (ProjectGallery.jsx and projectsLoader.js) that are unrelated to this implementation
- These pre-existing issues should be addressed separately
- The analytics implementation itself is clean and follows best practices
